where you can
sit back and relax

16:26.102 --> 16:28.334
while some peon
serves your every need.

16:29.601 --> 16:30.868
No beverage?

16:32.501 --> 16:33.667
Sorry.

16:37.767 --> 16:39.767
I never thought
I could have this much hate

16:39.802 --> 16:41.267
for an inanimate object.

16:41.302 --> 16:43.267
You mean Al?

16:43.302 --> 16:44.467
Yeah.

16:44.502 --> 16:45.767
And that car.

16:45.802 --> 16:47.400
Well, you know, Marce,

16:47.435 --> 16:50.601
the love of a nice automobile
is not just a guy thing.

16:50.636 --> 16:52.801
You can't say tell me
you never dated a guy

16:52.836 --> 16:53.834
because of his car.

16:53.869 --> 16:56.400
Never.
Come on.

16:56.435 --> 16:57.701
Well...

16:57.736 --> 16:59.501
Don't tell Steve,

16:59.536 --> 17:01.667
but there was this guy
in high school.

17:01.702 --> 17:03.100
He had a GTO.

17:03.135 --> 17:05.267
A black one.
Mmm.

17:05.301 --> 17:07.767
But I finally had
to break up with him, because-

17:07.801 --> 17:10.400
This is so disgusting-

17:10.435 --> 17:13.067
He wanted to, you know...

17:13.102 --> 17:15.032
get me in the back seat
of the car.

17:17.099 --> 17:18.467
So did you?

17:18.502 --> 17:19.867
Of course not.

17:19.903 --> 17:22.434
It's so dirty and tawdry.

17:22.469 --> 17:23.867
No, it isn't.

17:26.434 --> 17:27.567
You did that?

17:27.602 --> 17:29.267
Well, sure.

17:29.302 --> 17:32.634
It gets expensive chipping in
for a hotel every few days.

17:35.133 --> 17:37.000
I just never could.

17:37.035 --> 17:40.133
Steve wanted to,
but I'm glad we didn't.

17:40.168 --> 17:42.067
It's still our family car.

17:42.102 --> 17:45.167
We put groceries back there.

17:47.767 --> 17:51.033
Well, good news, girls.
We got the ashtray in.

17:51.068 --> 17:52.267
Where's Steve?

17:52.302 --> 17:54.868
He's still out there
playing with the top.

17:54.903 --> 17:56.801
You know, he gets carried away.

17:56.836 --> 17:58.000
I'm going to go get him.

17:58.035 --> 17:59.367
It's late,

17:59.402 --> 18:01.133
and we have to pick out
his clothes for tomorrow.

18:05.235 --> 18:06.534
Hello?

18:06.569 --> 18:08.334
Albany?

18:08.369 --> 18:10.133
Collect?
Hell, no, I'm not-

18:10.168 --> 18:12.234
We'll pay for the charges!

18:12.269 --> 18:13.234
Hello?

18:13.269 --> 18:15.534
Dr. Mustang?

18:15.569 --> 18:16.701
You got the ornament?!

18:16.736 --> 18:17.968
He got the little horse.

18:18.003 --> 18:19.534
Yee-ha.

18:19.569 --> 18:22.133
Yeah. You got
yourself a deal.

18:22.168 --> 18:24.801
I'll send the check
in the morning.

18:24.836 --> 18:26.801
Best to Mrs. Mustang.

18:26.836 --> 18:28.501
Wow! The little horse!

18:28.536 --> 18:29.934
We got to go tell Steve.

18:29.969 --> 18:31.734
Don't you two
want to be alone for this?

18:33.601 --> 18:34.734
Nah.

18:48.434 --> 18:51.000
Aw, isn't that sweet?

18:51.035 --> 18:53.934
It's their first time in a car.
Come on, honey.

18:53.969 --> 18:55.567
Okay.

18:55.602 --> 18:58.100
Wait a minute, Peg.

18:58.135 --> 18:59.467
Hey, Steve!

18:59.502 --> 19:01.367
We got the horse!

19:01.402 --> 19:02.634
All right!

19:08.067 --> 19:10.901
Well, it's almost time
for the unveiling.

19:10.936 --> 19:13.067
To tell you the truth,
I'm kind of curious.

19:13.102 --> 19:15.234
I haven't seen it
since they painted it.

19:16.602 --> 19:18.534
Aren't you getting excited?

19:18.569 --> 19:19.968
What's that supposed to mean?

19:22.000 --> 19:24.534
Come on, Marce.
It's been three weeks.

19:24.569 --> 19:25.934
You can look me in the eye.

19:27.767 --> 19:29.167
I can't help it.

19:29.202 --> 19:32.834
I'm still so embarrassed,
especially around Al.

19:32.869 --> 19:34.167
He doesn't say anything,

19:34.202 --> 19:35.968
but I know every time
he looks at me,

19:36.003 --> 19:38.634
he's thinking about
how he caught us in that car.

19:38.669 --> 19:41.534
Believe me, I've known him
a long time,

19:41.569 --> 19:44.701
and when Al's not talking,
he is not thinking.

19:46.968 --> 19:49.901
Girls, time for the unveiling.

19:49.936 --> 19:51.133
Big deal.

19:51.168 --> 19:52.834
Well, it will be
for you, Marce.

19:52.869 --> 19:55.100
This is your big chance
to see the outside of the car.

19:58.501 --> 19:59.601
Let's go.

20:06.767 --> 20:08.834
Gee. It's beautiful.

20:08.869 --> 20:10.133
Shut up, Peg.

20:10.168 --> 20:12.067
This is a big moment,

20:12.102 --> 20:13.667
and I want to make sure
it's right.

20:13.702 --> 20:15.133
Okay! Ready!

20:20.434 --> 20:24.000
Oh, Al, it really
is beautiful.

20:24.035 --> 20:25.667
Yeah, we know.

20:25.702 --> 20:27.834
Come on. Let's take
this baby for a spin.

20:27.869 --> 20:29.133
Girls, get in the back seat.

20:29.168 --> 20:31.167
Peg, Marcie can
show you the way.

20:34.501 --> 20:36.167
Steve, I'll drive.

20:36.202 --> 20:38.000
We'll take a nice spin
out in the country.

20:38.035 --> 20:40.501
You sit and lean coolly
out the window.

20:40.536 --> 20:42.234
We'll pretend
these are our mothers.

20:49.901 --> 20:52.133
* Born to be- *
* Born to be- *

21:03.035 --> 21:05.367
* Wild **
* Wild **

21:12.334 --> 21:14.434
I'm sorry about the car, honey.

21:14.469 --> 21:16.601
You couldn't have known
it was stolen.

21:18.133 --> 21:20.501
I think Al might have gone
a little overboard

21:20.536 --> 21:22.100
starting the fight
with that policeman.

21:22.135 --> 21:24.033
Now, Al just had it
in his head

21:24.068 --> 21:27.200
that the cop might
have been an impersonator.

21:27.235 --> 21:30.767
Sorry I put that
in your head, Al.

21:30.802 --> 21:32.334
By the way, Al?

21:32.369 --> 21:35.167
They say the effects
of the stun gun

21:35.202 --> 21:36.934
will wear off
in a few hours.

21:38.868 --> 21:41.300
Yeah, you know, you were
really holding your own

21:41.335 --> 21:43.601
until that angry mob showed up.

21:43.636 --> 21:46.400
I wonder where those farmers
got their stun guns.

21:47.968 --> 21:50.334
Well, there goes
our dream, old buddy.

21:52.133 --> 21:54.234
Al?

21:54.269 --> 21:56.567
They impounded the car.

21:56.602 --> 22:00.100
We'll never see it again,
except at the trial.

22:02.100 --> 22:04.300
Well, at least one good thing
came out of this.

22:04.335 --> 22:06.501
We found out we could all have
a good time together,

22:06.536 --> 22:08.634
and that's more important
than any car.

22:08.669 --> 22:09.634
Hear, hear.

22:09.669 --> 22:11.167
It's still early.

22:11.202 --> 22:13.200
Why don't we go out
and get some dinner,

22:13.235 --> 22:15.200
kick back,
and lick our wounds?

22:15.235 --> 22:17.234
Yeah. Let's go eat.

22:17.269 --> 22:18.834
How about Japanese?

22:18.869 --> 22:21.100
Thai? Moroccan?

22:21.135 --> 22:22.834
Whatever.
Al won't know the difference.

22:35.601 --> 22:39.100
* Born to be wild **

